{"filename":"introduction-to-react.md","title":"Introduction to React.js","headings":[{"level":2,"text":"Spectacle","id":"spectacle"},{"level":3,"text":"Code Slides","id":"code-slides"},{"level":3,"text":"Embedded Examples","id":"embedded-examples"},{"level":2,"text":"Feedback","id":"feedback"}],"date":"2017-05-18T00:00:00.000Z","image":"/images/posts/introduction_to_react/hero.jpg","body":{"t":"div","c":[{"t":"p","c":["I've been using ",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"https://facebook.github.io/react/","target":"_blank"},"c":["React"]}," for a few years now. If you read my ",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"/blog/posts/a-wedding-website/"},"c":["previous post"]},", then you know that it's my go-to library for creating user interfaces (including ",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"https://github.com/colinrcummings/blog"},"c":["this blog"]},"). I was recently asked to give a presentation on React at one of the software development Meetups I attend. I opted to introduce the library, walk through a couple of core concepts (with examples), do a few ad hoc demos and then leave the audience with some additional concepts, resources and tools. Below is an overview of ",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"http://formidable.com/open-source/spectacle/","target":"_blank"},"c":["Spectacle"]},", the library I used to create the presentation."]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":[{"t":"a","p":{"role":"button","class":"btn btn-default","href":"http://colinrcummings.github.io/meetup-react","target":"_blank"},"c":["View Presentation"]}]},"\n",{"t":"hr"},"\n",{"t":"h2","p":{"id":"spectacle"},"c":[{"t":"a","p":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#spectacle"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"Spectacle"]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["Spectacle bills itself as \"A React.js based library for creating sleek presentations\". It's ",{"t":"em","c":["awesome"]},". Being able to use components to compose a presentation about React felt right from the start. Out of the box, the library provides ",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"https://github.com/FormidableLabs/spectacle#tag-api","target":"_blank"},"c":["tags"]}," for core slideshow objects you're probably already familiar with from another ",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uNjxe8ShM-8","target":"_blank"},"c":["presentation program"]}," that shall not be named. Two things really set Spectacle apart from ",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"https://github.com/search?l=JavaScript&o=desc&q=presentation&s=stars&type=Repositories&utf8=%E2%9C%93","target":"_blank"},"c":["other web-based presentation tools"]},":"]},"\n",{"t":"h3","p":{"id":"code-slides"},"c":[{"t":"a","p":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#code-slides"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"Code Slides"]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["Embedding code in a presentation isn't new, but with the ",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"https://github.com/thejameskyle/spectacle-code-slide","target":"_blank"},"c":["spectacle-code-slide"]}," extension I was able to step through my example code with syntax highlighting and contextual notes."]},"\n",{"t":"div","p":{"class":"grid"},"c":["\n  ",{"t":"div","p":{"class":"col-2-12 hide-on-mobile"}},"\n  ",{"t":"div","p":{"class":"col-8-12"},"c":["\n    ",{"t":"div","p":{"class":"text-center margin-top-5"},"c":["\n      ",{"t":"div","c":["\n        ",{"t":"img","p":{"class":"img-rounded","src":"/images/posts/introduction_to_react/code_slide.gif","alt":"Code slide"}},"\n      "]},"\n    "]},"\n  "]},"\n  ",{"t":"div","p":{"class":"col-2-12 hide-on-mobile"}},"\n"]},"\n",{"t":"h3","p":{"id":"embedded-examples"},"c":[{"t":"a","p":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#embedded-examples"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"Embedded Examples"]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["Because the entire Spectacle presentation is a React component, I was able to embed my example components into my slides and interact with them live."]},"\n",{"t":"div","p":{"class":"grid"},"c":["\n  ",{"t":"div","p":{"class":"col-2-12 hide-on-mobile"}},"\n  ",{"t":"div","p":{"class":"col-8-12"},"c":["\n    ",{"t":"div","p":{"class":"text-center margin-top-5"},"c":["\n      ",{"t":"div","c":["\n        ",{"t":"img","p":{"class":"img-rounded","src":"/images/posts/introduction_to_react/interactive_example.gif","alt":"Interactive example"}},"\n      "]},"\n    "]},"\n  "]},"\n  ",{"t":"div","p":{"class":"col-2-12 hide-on-mobile"}},"\n"]},"\n",{"t":"hr"},"\n",{"t":"h2","p":{"id":"feedback"},"c":[{"t":"a","p":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#feedback"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"Feedback"]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["Have questions, comments or suggestions? Reach out to me on Twitter (",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"https://twitter.com/colinrcummings"},"c":["@colinrcummings"]},")."]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["â€” Colin"]}]}}